SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 67
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to recognize Carolyn McMahan, Clerk and
Master of the Sevier County Chancery Court, on
the occasion of her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm
throughout their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Carolyn McMahan is one such estimable person, who, having rendered
more than forty years of service as Clerk and Master of the Sevier County Chancery Court, has
taken her much-deserved retirement this year; and
WHEREAS, Ms. McMahan was appointed as Clerk and Master in January 1983 and has
since carried out her responsibilities with diligence, patience, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, prior to her station as Clerk and Master, Carolyn McMahan served as a
deputy clerk for twenty years, in which position she earned the respect and admiration of her
colleagues and her community alike; and
WHEREAS, her remarkable accomplishments as a public servant are directly
attributable to her reliance on the time-honored values of hard work and common sense and her
uncommon ability to work well with people from all walks of life; and
WHEREAS, Ms. McMahan is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service
that have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Carolyn McMahan for her
